{"key":"processedPost-8522838","value":{"id":8522838,"first":8521948,"last":8526090,"when":1213455020,"utime":"06/14/08 05:50 PM","content":"Agreed.&nbsp; Stack the lids and drill all twelve at once.&nbsp; Another tip is to drill the opposite direction they'll sit on the jars so the burrs don't puncture your filter.&nbsp; Since I use the lids rubber side up to make removal easier, I drill down from the rubber side, not the way they come shipped.<br /><br />If you use 1/4\" holes, don't drill more than one.&nbsp; Too much air will cause early pinning and drying of the grains.<br />RR","title":"Re: Lid Hole Drilling Tip","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}